##Anxiety of a boss in Zhejiang: I can't sleep without returning to work, I can't sleep even more after returning to work

Weixin caijingEleven

The function introduction by "CAIJING" Magazine Company Industry Report team to create, discuss the success or failure of the enterprise, explore the rise and fall of the industry, promote sunshine business

The following article comes from the attitude of a business insider, who silently looks at your fat cat

Quick View of financial hot spots, express professional position

Back to work. Turns out I was too optimistic

Rose Arrangement

Lone cloud | editor

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dictation: Mr. Yuan (owner of a textile enterprise in Zhejiang)

It has been more than ten days since our factory resumed work on February 17. We started with more than 150 staff, and now more than 300 staff.

I can't sleep until I get permission to go back to work, and I can't sleep until I get permission to go back to work.

At first I was worried about the staff coming back, and now I'm worried about the staff coming back, and there's no work for them to do.

At present, the government has introduced a lot of policies to help enterprises resume production, which is a good thing, but also really helped enterprises some.

But if the economy is to recover, I think the most important thing is to boost consumption, and the main driver of that is the banks.

The banks are now loosening their lending policies to businesses, with the best of intentions, but not the best of intentions. The most direct way is for the banks to rest for a few months.

We are a medium-sized textile enterprise. I do business at home and abroad. Mainly to a number of foreign well-known public clothing brands to provide fabrics, domestic also.

In Normal Times, I have over 500 employees, half of whom are from out of town.

February 14, I received the resumption of work, I was most worried about the return of field staff. I can't go back to work without the staff.

Our staff Anhui nationality is more, I prepared a bus to pick them up, but their village does not let out. It's no use giving us a work permit.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Later, the government introduced some policies to help enterprises resume work, Zhejiang even charter flights for our enterprises, chartered special trains to pick up workers. As a business, we're happy.

When I returned to work, there were only about 150 employees on duty. The machines in the workshop were running. At the time, I thought things were going great.

I predict that by early March, when all of our employees are on the job, my company will be back to normal.

So far, I'm too optimistic.

The more employees come back, the more pressure I get

Now my staff back to the city problem solved, has been on duty more than 300.

But there was a problem with my order.

The order that I am producing now is still the foreign order that I signed last year. According to the current ratio of staff to the post, another month of production will not have.

And I don't even know where my new order is going?

The other day, I had a chat with the chief purchasing officer of a well-known domestic public clothing brand. They, too, are in a dilemma.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When we talked about the next order, she said her company had a huge backlog of spring models in storage. Their boss is very headache, also very helpless, say everyday eye opens 4 million yuan to have no.

Their company is our main customer in the domestic market, if they order less, it means I have a hard time this year.

And my staff is still coming back, and as the boss, I can't say, "don't come. ". I don't have the heart.

The pressure's getting to me.

The more employees I have back, the more pressure I'm under. They come back, I can't let them idle, I had to do the finished goods of the main road, stacked in the warehouse.

I want to help them. They work for me. They want to live. They have children to educate, they have mortgages to pay for. But I finally or that Little Bird, want to fly always fly high.

Because that means I have to constantly turn my liquidity into unmarketable inventory.

I can do this for a month, two months, but can I do it for the third month?

I'm having a hard time.

I wish I could take all the blame, but I can't

In fact, there are many such enterprises, no single hand, or not many single, also have to go back to work.

I am still good, there are orders to do, I still have ten million working capital, some enterprises have no working capital long ago, if the production of goods can not sell, but also continue to produce, it is really too difficult.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Even so, I am anxious every day.

I buy raw materials, I produce inventory, my employees'salaries, the monthly bank interest I have to pay, and water, electricity, taxes, all add up to money.

For example, in February, my bank interest paid more than 500,000 yuan, the staff salary, water and electricity, as well as taxes, 7788 added up to more than 2 million yuan.

If more than 500 employees are on duty, the monthly salary will be three million RMB per month.

If I can't sell without an order, how many times can I pay three million in cash?

And no matter you produce, or stop production, your goods can be sold, or not sold, the bank's interest will still be paid.

Fortunately, our plant is their own, there is no rent problem, some enterprises also pay rent, so that enterprises will soon be dragged down.

So, from the bottom of my heart, I have 300 employees now and that's enough.

I wish I could lighten the burden on my country and shoulder all the problems myself, but my shoulders are too narrow and my burden is too heavy to last long.

Bank rate cuts are a drop in the bucket, not a cure

Now the government is trying to help us, and the banks are trying to help them get back to work, but whether the banks can put their policies into practice is another matter.

For example, on February 10, Zhejiang introduced the first batch of preferential enterprise policies.

The first of these states, "For existing stocks and loans, banks will calculate the current interest rate for February 2020 at no higher than the LPR interest rate for manufacturing, wholesale and retail industries, accommodation and catering industries and other industries seriously affected by the epidemic, with the highest interest-free policy. "

Is there an operational standard for this "maximum" ? No.

The "highest" is when the bank calls the shots.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
And that rule applies to February. What about March?

Our company belongs to the manufacturing industry. Do we enjoy the "highest" ? No.

We had some banks in February that were supposed to be paying 550,000 or so in interest, and in this crisis, they gave us a discount of 50,000 or more.

This kind of interest rate cut is really a drop in the bucket for our company.

In addition, the bank solves the loan to the enterprise, I thought this kind of method cures the symptom but not the root cause. And the banks have their own criteria for what firms they lend to, and if they do, it is limited.

Besides, some of the businesses, you lent him as much money as you could, and instead of giving him five million dollars, you increased your efforts and gave him ten million dollars.

It seems that this is a good thing Ah, "you really love me Ah, " It seems that he has a lot of working capital Ah, but the same, he has more debt, your bank added more interest.

The problem is, he can't sell what he makes, and all his money becomes inventory, and eventually your bank not only doesn't help him, it adds to his stress.

In this case, you ask the Bank "Tomorrow Still Love Me" , obviously impossible.

Therefore, lending to enterprises is only temporary, and can not fundamentally solve the problem, it is a palliative.

The solution to the current dilemma lies in the mobilization of consumption

Boosting consumption is the only way to solve this dilemma.

When we get this epidemic under control, when we let it all go, when we get consumption going, that's what's going to matter.

Now there are more and more people on the streets of Hangzhou, and many places that can be opened are also opening up. That's a good thing.

But this is only temporary, even if there is consumption, it is retaliatory, and will not last, waiting for people pocket money consumption, consumption will be stagnant.

As a result, the purchasing power of society as a whole would decline, and a cascade of adverse reactions would ensue, with businesses closing and employees losing their jobs.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Maybe 80% of US have a mortgage. Before most of us buy a house, we have a good plan, the wife's money to live, including all aspects of education, as well as clothing, food and shelter; the husband's money to pay the mortgage.

But now faced with such a sudden epidemic, one of the husband and wife laid off, or both of the husband and wife did not lay off, but wages have become less, this is a family, are hard hit.

When a family's plans are disrupted and mortgage payments become a problem, what are they going to spend it on?

The decline in the purchasing power of individuals, directly affected by the enterprise.

Companies, like individuals, have a monthly production plan. How much is the monthly operating cost of the enterprise? How about the list.

After such a crisis, everyone's plans were shattered.

For example, our textile industry, the people have no money, with less money to buy clothes. The manufacturer of the garment will reduce the volume of production, and with that comes the chain reaction, which is our fabric industry.

We have fewer orders, and the first thing that comes to my mind is layoffs, and I'm probably going to have to close up shop. This means that more than 500 employees in our factory will face the problem of re-employment.

In this way, our ecological chain is completely broken, we will enter a loop.

If the economy is to recover, we need to find a way to break through the whole ecological chain, and to break through the whole ecological chain, it is impossible to solve the problem by only returning to work.

The only real boost to consumption would come from a pause in banking

The only direct way to boost consumption now is for banks to stop interest rates, not cut them. Any rate cut would be a drop in the bucket for individuals and businesses.

Businesses can take a breather if they stop paying interest on their mortgages for a few months, and people won't lose their jobs. If they stop paying their mortgages for another few months, the economy will slowly recover.

The bank should do more to help the needy, not just icing on the cake.

When consumption pulls up, all aspects of natural society will be better. This time, you let the enterprise not to resume work, they will do everything possible to resume work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Now the government has the policy, but the question is whether the bank has implemented the policy. Because each bank's loan guarantee pattern is different, most of our enterprises will put the loan in several banks.

For example, our company, I have credit relations with several banks, our industrial and commercial bank has lent 20 million yuan, agricultural bank has also lent 20 million yuan, and so on.

In this way, each bank who will not give the enterprise interest-free, who did not, is tantamount to their own interests to others.

But in the long run, when companies fail, the economy as a whole, and the banks, fail. When an avalanche comes, no snowflake can escape it.

Banks should take a long-term view, stick together to keep warm and act in a unified way. If the banks don't act, and each does its own thing, that's dangerous, and a whole range of social problems will follow.

I have been in the textile industry for more than 30 years, and have encountered various difficulties, but the way is more difficult than.

Generally speaking, the situation is still in a positive direction. We in Hangzhou have not had any new confirmed cases for eight days, and the government's preferential policies for enterprises are on the increase.

I believe that we can get through this difficult time if we work together with the government.
